INSERT INTO `titles` VALUES ('0047d26457fdb00cedb03298f3507228',111161,'The Shawshank Redemption',1994,'http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/M/MV5BMTYzMzA2Nzc2Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMzQwMTgxMQ@@._V1._SX78_SY140_.jpg','/rg/photos-title/still_frame-1/media/rm1818789888/tt0111161','/video/screenplay/vi415302425/',0.92,458831,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1995-03-01','1 March 1995','Fear can hold you prisoner. Hope can set you free.','Two imprisoned men bond over a number of years, finding solace and eventual redemption through acts of common decency.','Nominated for 7 Oscars. Another 11 wins & 13 nominations','Rita Hayworth and the Shawshank Redemption (USA) (working title)',142,'Color (Technicolor)','1.85 : 1','R','At the end of the movie, there is a dedication to Allen Greene. He was Frank Darabont\'s agent and also a close personal friend. He died just before the completion of the movie due to AIDS complications.','Continuity: When Andy comes out of the cell in his first morning in prison, Red is shown wearing a shirt with a number that begins with 311, not beginning with a 302 which is the number on his shirt in the rest of the movie.'),('0163a27a977adac18473999cac076658',61811,'In the Heat of the Night',1967,'http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/M/MV5BMTg5MTEwODM4NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTYwNDIyNDk5._V1._SX98_SY140_.jpg','/rg/photos-title/still_frame-1/media/rm1702402048/tt0061811','/video/imdblink/vi763757849/',0.81,21023,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1968-03-01','1 March 1968','They got a murder on their hands . . . they don\'t know what to do with it.','An African American detective is asked to investigate a murder in a racist southern town.','Won 5 Oscars. Another 17 wins & 12 nominations',NULL,109,'Color','1.85 : 1','Approved','The scene that took place at the sheriff\'s house featured dialog that came out of improvisations between Sidney Poitier and Rod Steiger.','Revealing mistakes: It\'s still early morning when Harvey Oberst is running for Arkansas (Tibbs wants to catch the noon train). The sun should b